---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Guides — chulbuji.com"
  description="Practical methodology documents on AI collaboration and execution workflows."
>
  <div class="guides-container">

    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>Guides</h1>
      <p>Practical methodology documents on how to actually work alongside AI.<br>Focused on execution flow over theory.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="guides-grid">

      <article class="guide-card">
        <div class="guide-meta">
          <span class="guide-tag guide-tag--primary">Methodology</span>
          <time>May 31, 2026</time>
        </div>
        <a href="/en/guides/vibe-coding-guide/" class="guide-title">
          Vibe Coding Guide: Building an App with AI Without Deep Coding Knowledge
        </a>
        <p class="guide-excerpt">You don't need deep coding knowledge to build an MVP with AI. This guide covers planning documents, AI role separation, and validation criteria — the practical end-to-end flow of vibe coding using ChatGPT, Claude Code, and Codex.</p>
        <div class="guide-tags">
          <span>Vibe Coding</span>
          <span>AI Coding</span>
          <span>Claude Code</span>
          <span>MVP</span>
        </div>
        <a href="/en/guides/vibe-coding-guide/" class="guide-link">Read the guide →</a>
      </article>

      <article class="guide-card">
        <div class="guide-meta">
          <span class="guide-tag guide-tag--insight">Operational Insight</span>
          <time>May 25, 2026</time>
        </div>
        <a href="/en/insight/vibe-coding-harness-design/" class="guide-title">
          The Core of Vibe Coding Was the Harness, Not the Code
        </a>
        <p class="guide-excerpt">Before building Commit Hero, I designed the judgment structure first. Running Deep Interviews to set direction, then defining scope through Plan, Design, and AGENTS.md before implementation — the experience confirmed that the human role in vibe coding is harness design, not coding.</p>
        <div class="guide-tags">
          <span>Vibe Coding</span>
          <span>Harness Design</span>
          <span>Codex</span>
          <span>AI Product Build</span>
        </div>
        <a href="/en/insight/vibe-coding-harness-design/" class="guide-link">Read the insight →</a>
      </article>

      <article class="guide-card">
        <div class="guide-meta">
          <span class="guide-tag guide-tag--insight">Operational Insight</span>
          <time>May 25, 2026</time>
        </div>
        <a href="/en/insight/codex-workflow-design-over-prompting/" class="guide-title">
          What I Learned from Codex Practice — Workflow Design Matters More Than Commands
        </a>
        <p class="guide-excerpt">Running Codex vibe coding practice revealed that AI coding agents move autonomously through the entire task when given a broad goal. The real capability in AI development is not prompt writing — it is designing the sequence of work, the permissions granted, and the stop conditions.</p>
        <div class="guide-tags">
          <span>Codex</span>
          <span>Vibe Coding</span>
          <span>Workflow Design</span>
          <span>AI Agent</span>
        </div>
        <a href="/en/insight/codex-workflow-design-over-prompting/" class="guide-link">Read the insight →</a>
      </article>

      <article class="guide-card">
        <div class="guide-meta">
          <span class="guide-tag guide-tag--insight">Operational Insight</span>
          <time>May 28, 2026</time>
        </div>
        <a href="/en/insight/ai-role-separation-diverge-and-converge/" class="guide-title">
          Divergence Happens in a New Window, Convergence Happens at HQ
        </a>
        <p class="guide-excerpt">As AI tools multiply, role separation comes first. A new GPT window works as an external thinking space for divergence without inherited context, while Meta Chulbuji absorbs the results into existing projects as the operating HQ. The key was not blocking divergence, but building a structure that recovers it as an asset.</p>
        <div class="guide-tags">
          <span>AI Role Separation</span>
          <span>ChatGPT</span>
          <span>AI Workflow</span>
          <span>Operating Philosophy</span>
        </div>
        <a href="/en/insight/ai-role-separation-diverge-and-converge/" class="guide-link">Read the insight →</a>
      </article>

    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .guides-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2.5rem 1.25rem 4rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .page-header h1 {
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 1.4rem + 1.75vw, 2.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .page-header p {
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .guides-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .guide-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 1.75rem 2rem;
    background: white;
    transition: box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }

  .guide-card:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .guide-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
  }

  .guide-tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .guide-tag--primary {
    color: var(--primary-color);
    background: #f0f0ff;
  }

  .guide-tag--insight {
    color: #2e7d32;
    background: #e8f5e9;
  }

  time {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .guide-title {
    display: block;
    font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 1rem + 0.3125vw, 1.25rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-color);
    text-decoration: none;
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin-bottom: 0.875rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .guide-title:hover {
    color: var(--primary-color);
  }

  .guide-excerpt {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.75;
    margin-bottom: 1.125rem;
  }

  .guide-tags {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .guide-tags span {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #777;
    background: #f5f5f5;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .guide-link {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--primary-color);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .guide-link:hover {
    color: var(--secondary-color);
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .guides-container {
      padding: 2rem 1rem 3rem;
    }

    .guide-card {
      padding: 1.25rem 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
